 different system from d20, from which I personally need a short break.<br>
<br>
Based on our discussions of what each person is considering character-wise, a very strong team is forming up. I would ask that each player be as familiar as possible (i.e. read the books) on their area of specialty(Magic, Muscle, Rigging, Decking). I plan to incorporate all aspects of the shadowrun world into a campaign, so be ready.<br>
<br>
Since Witchfire is winding down (about 3 weeks left, according to Dave), now is the time to get those characters ready. As you all know character creation can be right time consuming (so many nuyen, so little time), so get to work on tweaking those starting characters now.<br>
<br>
It has also been suggested that we do some small preludes to help each person get a refresher on the rules and the world of 2061. I think this is a good idea, and am willing to do short individual games for the players in pairs. Therefore we could do 2 characters each for 3 weeks which would time itself nicely with the grand conclusion of the Witchfire Campaign. <br>
<br>
So what do you think?<br>
Feel free to post ideas, comments, character ideas, whatever, as it pertains to Shadowrun. And remember to watch your back, keep your ammo handy, and never cut a deal with a dragon.<br>
<br>
Your Guide to the Sixth World,<br>
<br>
